  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed and six flagged as epistemic gaps. The intended use scope — steady-state VAD operation at 2500–5000 RPM with hematocrit 35–45%, for pre-market submission support — is described in the Claim and Requirement prose. The package conforms to ProfileMinimal and the structured hasContextOfUse node is intentionally absent; reviewers should not infer that use-scope constraints have been formally bounded.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credibility-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-measurements"
  ],
